 By Theorem 1.3.10 from the textbook,
 we can write:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
A(\vec{x}_{1}+\vec{x}_{h})=A\vec{x}_{1}+A\vec{x}_{h}=\vec{b}+\vec{0}=\vec{b},
\]

\end_inset

and so 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{x}_{1}+\vec{x}_{h}$
\end_inset

 solves the system 
\begin_inset Formula $A\vec{x}=\vec{b}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

